# API Flow Diagrams - Knowledge Sharing Tech Community

## Overview
This document contains detailed Mermaid flow diagrams for API request lifecycle, validation, authentication, error handling, recovery, and moderation flows.

---

## 1. Request Lifecycle Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant LoadBalancer
    participant APIGateway
    participant AuthService
    participant RateLimiter
    participant ValidationService
    participant BusinessService
    participant Database
    participant Cache
    participant AuditService
    
    Client->>LoadBalancer: HTTP Request
    LoadBalancer->>APIGateway: Forward Request
    
    APIGateway->>RateLimiter: Check Rate Limit
    RateLimiter-->>APIGateway: Rate Limit Status
    
    alt Rate Limit Exceeded
        APIGateway-->>Client: 429 Too Many Requests
    else Rate Limit OK
        APIGateway->>AuthService: Validate Token
        AuthService-->>APIGateway: Authentication Result
        
        alt Authentication Failed
            APIGateway-->>Client: 401 Unauthorized
        else Authentication Success
            APIGateway->>ValidationService: Validate Request
            ValidationService-->>APIGateway: Validation Result
            
            alt Validation Failed
                APIGateway-->>Client: 400 Bad Request
            else Validation Success
                APIGateway->>BusinessService: Process Request
                
                alt Cache Hit
                    BusinessService->>Cache: Get Cached Data
                    Cache-->>BusinessService: Cached Data
                else Cache Miss
                    BusinessService->>Database: Query Data
                    Database-->>BusinessService: Query Results
                    BusinessService->>Cache: Update Cache
                end
                
                BusinessService-->>APIGateway: Processed Result
                APIGateway->>AuditService: Log Request
                AuditService-->>APIGateway: Log Confirmed
                APIGateway-->>Client: 200 OK + Response
            end
        end
    end
```

