## 2. Validation Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Incoming Request] --> B[Schema Validation]
    B --> C{Schema Valid?}
    C -->|No| D[400 Bad Request]
    C -->|Yes| E[Business Rule Validation]
    
    E --> F{Business Rules Valid?}
    F -->|No| G[422 Unprocessable Entity]
    F -->|Yes| H[Permission Validation]
    
    H --> I{User Has Permission?}
    I -->|No| J[403 Forbidden]
    I -->|Yes| K[Resource Validation]
    
    K --> L{Resource Exists?}
    L -->|No| M[404 Not Found]
    L -->|Yes| N[State Validation]
    
    N --> O{Resource State Valid?}
    O -->|No| P[409 Conflict]
    O -->|Yes| Q[Rate Limit Validation]
    
    Q --> R{Rate Limit OK?}
    R -->|No| S[429 Too Many Requests]
    R -->|Yes| T[Content Validation]
    
    T --> U{Content Appropriate?}
    U -->|No| V[451 Unavailable For Legal Reasons]
    U -->|Yes| W[Validation Passed]
    
    D --> X[Return Error Response]
    G --> X
    J --> X
    M --> X
    P --> X
    S --> X
    V --> X
    
    W --> Y[Proceed to Business Logic]
    X --> Z[Log Validation Failure]
```

